  "texts": [
    "In summary, this study not only highlights the potential of LLMs in materials science, but also lays the groundwork for future explorations in three main strategies: improving context quality, using enhanced TT, and employing capable VMs.",
    "Future explorations could range from improving the core reasoning capabilities of LLMs to adapting them for more diverse and complex scientific applications, thereby broadening their utility and impact in the scientific community.1)1Performance Evaluation: How does KDD compare in efficiency and effectiveness against traditional DDD baseline methods in AAC design?",
    "2) Contextual Quality: How does the level of specificity and detail in the context provided to LLMs affect the effectiveness of the AAC design process?",
    "3) Standard Feedback Design Loop (SFDL) vs.",
    "Testing and Verification Design Loop (TVDL): How do outcomes of a standard implementation compare against an extended TT strategy?"
  ]
}